MetaVerse Walking Simulator: Game Requirements Document
Game Concept
Create a satirical walking simulator set in a simplified "metaverse" environment where all users appear as identical avatars, reflecting the meme's commentary on virtual reality platforms.
Core Mechanics
Avatar System

All players should appear as identical stylized avatars wearing dark shirts with buttons
Each player should have their username displayed above their avatar
No avatar customization in the initial release (to emphasize the satirical uniformity)

Movement & Controls

First-person and third-person camera options
WASD/arrow keys for movement
Mouse for camera control
Spacebar for jumping
Simple collision detection with environment objects

Environment

Create a simplified, low-poly world featuring recognizable landmarks:

Eiffel Tower
Sagrada Familia cathedral
Rolling green hills
Simple trees


Use a bright, vibrant color palette with minimal texturing
Implement a perpetually clear blue sky

Multiplayer Features

Support for at least 20 simultaneous players
Simple proximity-based voice chat
Player position syncing
Player join/leave notifications

User Interface

Minimalistic UI with:

Player name display
Connected users list
Simple emoji reaction system
Settings menu (volume, graphics, controls)



Technical Requirements
Three.js Implementation

Use Three.js for 3D rendering
Implement efficient low-poly models to ensure good performance
Utilize WebGL for rendering
Support for desktop and mobile browsers

Networking

WebSocket connection for real-time player position updates
Simple server architecture to handle player connections
Data optimization to minimize bandwidth usage

Performance Targets

60 FPS on mid-range hardware
Mobile-friendly version at 30 FPS
Optimize asset loading for faster initial experience

